{"id":"sheminith","term":"Sheminith","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Eight; octave, a musical term, supposed to denote the lowest note sung by men’s voices (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 15:21\">1 Chr. 15:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 6:1\">Ps. 6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 12:1\">12</a>, title).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 15:21","Psalms 6:1","Psalms 12:1"]}